      - The current memory schema just stores raw text and read() blindly returns everything, so there’s no structured way to link “Alice” to “favorite color.” The LLM never sees facts with explicit subject/predicate/value, so even though “Alice’s favorite color is blue” might be written, the query “What is Alice’s favorite color?” can’t match it. 
      - There’s no filtering in read(), so the assistant either gets overwhelmed by the whole store or returns nothing useful; we need a targeted retrieval strategy.
      - The instructions do not describe how to populate structured observations or queries, so the LLM doesn’t know what JSON to emit.
      
